comment:
* Represents an operation upon two {@code double}-valued operands and producing a * {@code double}-valued result. This is the primitive type specialization of * {@link BinaryOperator} for {@code double}. * *

This is a functional interface * whose functional method is {@link #applyAsDouble(double, double)}. * * @see BinaryOperator * @see DoubleUnaryOperator * @since 1.8

methods.name: double applyAsDouble(double left, double right)
methods.comment:
* Applies this operator to the given operands.
     *
     * @param left the first operand
     * @param right the second operand
     * @return the operator result
